<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Amaprop yr attrib loss shrinks.</title>
<headline>Amaprop yr attrib loss shrinks.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended March 31</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>Shr, (cts)</p>
<p>    - headline profit     45.63	 vs 72.43</p>
<p>    - Loss per share	17.42	 vs 72.43</p>
<p>    Final div none making 10.0 cts    vs 25.0 cts</p>
<p>    Attrib loss	     8.80	  vs 48.97</p>
<p>    Pre-tax loss	    15.36	 vs 85.55</p>
<p>    Tax			 2.76	  vs 20.66</p>
<p>    Interest paid	   24.44	 vs 28.57</p>
<p>    Turnover		  224.50	vs 272.96</p>
<p>Full name: Anglo American Properties Ltd</p>
<p>    Share of associates'  7.09 loss   vs 0.03 profit</p>
<p>    Exceptional items     49.28 loss  vs 128.78 loss</p>
<p>NOTE - Directors said profits from the estate division would continue to decline due to the depetion of stock. The Carlton Hotel would also continue to realise losses an the future operation of the hotel was dependent on the granting of a casino licence.</p>
<p>Income from property investments would come under pressure because of declining rentals, they said.</p>
<p>However, largely because of interest earned on surplus funds, earnings before exceptional items for coming year was expected to reflect an improvement over the 1997 results.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
